** (failure after windows upgrade) --> start > settings > system > recovery > go back            for 10 days only 
** (System Won't Boot After Upgrade) 
         (1) accessing WinRE : 1- power on the computer                    "hard reboot"
                               2- As soon as you see the Windows logo or the manufacturer's logo, press and hold the power button until the device forces a shutdown
                               3- Repeat this process 3 times
                               4- On the 4th attempt, Windows will detect a boot failure and automatically enter the "Automatic Repair" mode
                               5- When the blue screen appears, navigate to --> choose an option > Troubleshoot > Advanced options
         (2) from Advanced options >> startup repair            restarting the device                                                      
      or (3) Safe Mode if startup repair doesn't resolve the issue : from Advanced options >> Startup Settings > after Restart > Enable Safe Mode
      or (4) from Advanced options >> command prompt   ex : chkdsk /r /f , sfc /scannow , bootrec /rebuildbcd
      or (5) from Advanced options >> system restore      to restore the old version            
** (move the files in case WinRE) : 1- access WinRE  2- Troubleshoot > Advanced options > command prompt 
                                    3- notepad + enter (file explorer) or write commands 

** (time lagging) --> GUI : 
                      win + I (settings) > time&language > turn on set time automatically 
                  --> CLI :
                      w32tm /resync     Force immediate sync without changing settings (must run as administrators)  

** (upgrading the hard from HDD to SSD) using SATA to USB cable: 
1 - Connect: Plug the new SSD into the SATA-to-USB cable and connect it to the laptop.
2 - Initialize: Use "Disk Management" in Windows to make sure the new SSD is recognized.
3 - Clone: Use cloning software (like Macrium Reflect or Acronis) to copy the entire HDD to the SSD.
4 - Swap: Power off the laptop, remove the old HDD, and physically install the SSD inside.
5 - Boot: Turn on the laptop and enjoy the high speed!




























